content:
Add Your Website to the CORS Allowlist

You need to add the URLs of the web pages where you intend to add the chat window to the CORS allowlist in your org.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Embedded Service setup node is available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To set up Embedded Chat:	Customize Application AND Modify Metadata

The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026. To avoid service interruptions to your customers, migrate to Messaging for In-App and Web before that date.

You can use HTTP and HTTPS domains with Embedded Chat. The protocol for the URL that you allowlist must match the URL in the website or Experience site endpoint in the code snippet.

From Setup, enter CORS in the Quick Find box, then select CORS.
Select New.
Enter an origin URL pattern.
The origin URL pattern must include the HTTP or HTTPS protocol and a domain name. The wildcard character (*) is supported and must be in front of a second-level domain name.
The origin URL pattern can include a port.

To add Your website to the CORS allowlist:

- From Setup, select CORS.
- Select New.
- Enter an origin URL pattern with the HTTP or HTTPS protocol and a domain name.
title: Setting up Embedded Chat in Salesforce Service Cloud
